HEADWORD: Warpath
<hw>War"path`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The route taken by a
party of Indians going on a warlike expedition.</def>
<rj><au>Schoolcraft.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>On the warpath</b></col>, <cd>on a hostile expedition;
hence, colloquially, about to attack a person or measure.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warper</ent>⟦br⟧
